OL,3,CAre Wales' women on course for another
OL,4,Cwooden spoon?
OL,6,FThe Women's Six Nations swings back
OL,7,Finto action this weekend after a
OL,8,Ffallow week.
OL,10,FBut, with two games remaining, Wales
OL,11,Fremain on a painfully familiar course.
OL,13,FDefeats to Ireland and Italy in their
OL,14,Ffinal contests would condemn them to a
OL,15,Fthird consecutive wooden spoon,
OL,16,Ffollowing in the footsteps of their
OL,17,Fmale counterparts.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
